    • doReport

      void doReport()
      Reporting 1 (Task 1) Get the top N most popular names at birth over a given period.

      To be triggered by the "REPORT" button on the Reporting 1 Tab. Perform input validation on user inputs on Reporting 1 tab, pop alert with reason if inputs are invalid. Otherwise, pop out a table to show the top N most popular names over a given period, and provide a summary in the textAreaConsole.

    • doNamePopularityQuery

      void doNamePopularityQuery()
      Reporting 2 (Task 2) Report the popularity of a particular name over a given period.

      To be triggered by the "REPORT" button on the Reporting 2 Tab. Perform input validation on user inputs on Reporting 2 tab, pop alert with reason if inputs are invalid. Otherwise, pop out a table to show the popularity of a particular name over a given period, and provide a summary in the textAreaConsole.

    • doNameTrendQuery

      void doNameTrendQuery()
      Reporting 3 (Task 3) Get trend of Top N names between two years

      To be triggered by the "REPORT" button on the Reporting 3 Tab. Perform input validation on user inputs on Reporting 3 tab, pop alert with reason if user inputs are invalid. Otherwise, show a summary of the name trend and pop table with detailed data.

    • doBabyNameRecommendation

      void doBabyNameRecommendation()
      Application 1 (Task 4) Get recommendations on names for newborn babies

      To be triggered by the "Start Query" button on the Application 1 Tab. Perform input validation on user inputs on Application 1 tab, pop alert with reason if user inputs are invalid. Otherwise, show recommended name for baby boy and recommended name for baby girl.

    • doSoulmateRecommendation

      void doSoulmateRecommendation()
      Application 2 (Task 5) Predict name of a compatible pairs (soulmate name).

      To be triggered by the "Get Prediction" button on the Application 2 Tab. Perform input validation on user inputs on Application 2 tab, pop alert with reason if user inputs are invalid. Otherwise, show a name of a compatible pairs (soulmate) according to the inputs.

    • doCompatibilityPrediction

      void doCompatibilityPrediction()
      Application 3 (Task 6) Predict compatibility of a pair

      To be triggered by the "PREDICT" button on the Application 3 Tab. Perform input validation on user inputs on Application 3 Tab, pop alert with reason if user inputs are invalid. Otherwise, show the compatibility in percentage (correct to 2 d.p.).
